    ns1:inpersonHours "64 horas (41%)"@es ;
    ns1:numberOfCredits 6.0 ;
    ns1:otherInformation """The subject supports the Sustainable Development Objectives from the United Nations, making emphasis in the following items:
- Increase the number of people with the professional and technical skills needed to access employment, decent work and entrepreneurship.
- Ensure that all students acquire the knowledge and skills necessary to promote sustainable development.
- Develop reliable, sustainable, resilient and quality infrastructure, with particular emphasis on affordable and equitable access for all.
- Increase access to ICTs and strive to provide universal and affordable access to the Internet in the least developed countries.
- Improve cooperation on and access to science, technology and innovation, and increase knowledge sharing on mutually agreed terms."""@es ;
    ns1:periodEndingMonth "Junio"@es ;
    ns1:periodStartingMonth "Febrero"@es ;
    ns1:teachingPeriod "2025-26" ;
    ns1:teachingPeriodMonths "Febrero-Junio"@es ;
    ns1:totalHours "64 horas"@es ;
    schema:activitiesWorkload "100%"@es ;
    schema:courseSchedule <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/93000806/2025-26/eventSchedule> ;
    schema:description """The course begins with an in-depth exploration of Media Asset Management (MAM), teaching students how to efficiently organize, store, and retrieve multimedia content such as images, audio, video, and text documents. It covers the essential functionalities of MAM systems and their importance in the media and entertainment industry. Students will also learn about techniques and standards for integrating and using metadata in multimedia systems, enhancing the organization, search, and management of multimedia content. The course then delves into multimedia analysis, covering audio, video, and text data. Methodologies for audio data analysis include signal processing techniques and the use of artificial intelligence for feature extraction and pattern recognition, such as audio classification, speech-to-text transcription, and emotion detection. Video data analysis covers visual feature extraction, object tracking, activity recognition, and video content indexing, with a focus on AI applications for enhancing video quality and event detection. Text data analysis involves text mining and natural language processing (NLP) techniques for information extraction, text classification, sentiment analysis, and automatic text summarization, emphasizing AI to improve analysis accuracy and efficiency.
The curriculum further explores multimedia information retrieval systems, teaching students to design and evaluate systems that enable efficient search and retrieval of multimedia content from large databases using content-based and metadata-based search techniques. Techniques for creating user profiles and recommending multimedia content are also covered, including collecting and analyzing user data to personalize user experiences with content-based systems, collaborative filtering, and hybrid approaches. Finally, the course addresses trends and pattern analysis in multimedia data, teaching students to identify and analyze trends in large multimedia datasets using advanced data analysis and machine learning techniques. Practical applications such as social media monitoring, user behavior analysis, and predicting future trends in multimedia content consumption are discussed.
The subject has a strong practical component aim, and so it is complemented with several laboratory exercises, according to the Project Based Learning philosophy. Resources from the Laboratory of Signals and Communications will be used, including workstations."""@es ;
    schema:director <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/alberto.belmonte%40upm.es> ;
    schema:inLanguage "Inglés/Castellano"@es ;
    schema:instructor <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/alberto.belmonte%40upm.es>,
        <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/javier.casajus%40upm.es>,
        <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/jl.blanco%40upm.es>,
        <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/jm.menendez%40upm.es> ;
    schema:name "Diseño de Sistemas de Datos para Media"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/93000806/2025-26/CE1> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CE1" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Capacidad para aplicar métodos de la teoría de la información, la modulación adaptativa y codificación de canal, así como técnicas avanzadas de procesado digital de señal a los sistemas de comunicaciones y audiovisuales."@es .

