<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/93000806/2025-26/evaluation> a ns1:EvaluationSystem ;
    ns1:evaluationDescription """Progressive Evaluation:
It consists of three main components.
Laboratories: Four laboratory sessions will be held throughout the course, each lasting 4 hours and divided into two parts. During each lab, students will be given problems to solve, which must be submitted upon completion. Attendance is mandatory. If a student does not attend or fails to achieve the minimum required score of 4 points in any lab, they will automatically be redirected to the global evaluation system.
Home Assignments: After each lab, students will be assigned a take-home task covering both the theoretical and practical content. A total of 4 assignments will be given, and a minimum score of 3.5 points in each is required in order to be averaged with the rest of the components. The submission deadline is 3 days before the final exam.
Final Exam: A final exam will cover the entire syllabus. A minimum score of 3.5 points is required for the exam to be averaged with the rest of the components.
The final grade will be the weighted average of labs, home assignments, and the final exam, using the percentages specified in the course guide.
Global Evaluation:
It consists of two main components.
Home Assignments: Students must complete the 4 assignments proposed during the course. A minimum score of 5 points in each is required to be averaged with the exam. The submission deadline is 3 days before the exam.
Final Exam: A comprehensive exam covering the full syllabus. A minimum score of 5 points is required in order to be averaged with the assignments.
The final grade will be the weighted average of the home assignments and the final exam, according to the criteria specified in the course guide.
Extraordinary Evaluation:
It consists of two main components.
Home Assignments: Students must complete the 4 assignments proposed during the course. A minimum score of 5 points in each is required to be averaged with the exam. The submission deadline is 3 days before the extraordinary exam date.
Final Exam: A comprehensive exam covering the full syllabus. A minimum score of 5 points is required in order to be averaged with the assignments.
The final grade will be the weighted average of the home assignments and the final exam, as detailed in the course guide.
Additional Considerations:
If a student fails to submit one of the evaluation components or does not meet the required minimum score, the final grade for that exam period will not exceed 4.5 points. This applies to all types of evaluations described above.
Any evaluation or submission may require a complementary oral assessment by the instructor to verify that the work was completed by the student without inappropriate assistance from AI systems, or that AI was only used where explicitly allowed."""@es ;
